-- Unseeded Berlocq Upsets Verdasco to Win Swedish Tennis Open
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2013-07-14T16:54:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-14/unseeded-berlocq-upsets-verdasco-to-win-swedish-tennis-open.html
Argentina’s Carlos Berlocq defeated
Fernando Verdasco of Spain in straight sets today to win
tennis’s Swedish Open, his first ATP singles title.  Unseeded Berlocq beat the No. 8 seed 7-5, 6-1 in Bastad.  In Stuttgart, Germany, fifth-seed Fabio Fognini of  Italy 
beat No. 2 Philipp Kohlschreiber of Germany 5-7, 6-4, 6-4
in the final of the ATP Mercedes Cup.  No. 3 seed Simona Halep of Romania beat Yvonne Meusburger
of Austria 6-3, 6-7 (7-9), 6-1 in the final of the WTA Budapest
Grand Prix. It was Halep’s third WTA title this year.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Christopher Elser  at   celser@bloomberg.net . 